title: shNC-exo1
characteristics_ch1.1: cell type: human breast carcinoma cell line
growth_protocol_ch1: Approximately 5.5 × 106 of MDA-MB-231 cells (shNC or shMCU stable clones) were cultured in DMEM containing 10% exosome-free FBS with a 150 mm dish for 48 hrs.
extract_protocol_ch1: The exosomes were isolated and purified using a PEG6000-based enrichment and ultracentrifugation. Exosomal miRNA was isolated using miRNeasy Mini Kit (#217004, QIAGEN) according to the user's instructions.Preparation of small RNA libraries was done using the CleanTag Small RNA library prep kit (TriLink Biotechnologies, USA).
extract_protocol_ch1.1: RNA libraries were prepared for sequencing using standard Illumina protocols.
data_processing: Illumina Casava1.7 software used for basecalling.
data_processing.1: Reads Per Kilobase of exon per Megabase of library size (RPKM) were calculated using a protocol from Chepelev et al., Nucleic Acids Research, 2009. In short, exons from all isoforms of a gene were merged to create one meta-transcript. The number of reads falling in the exons of this meta-transcript were counted and normalized by the size of the meta-transcript and by the size of the library.
data_processing.2: The comparison of sRNA to Genbank and Rfam was performed using blast or bowtie, rRNA, scRNA, snoRNA, snRNA and tRNA were then screened and removed.
data_processing.3: The mapping of sequencing reads to the human genome (hg19) was performed using miRDeep2 software package.
data_processing.5: Supplementary_files_format_and_content: Excel 97-2003 files include RPKM values for each Sample.
